ss suit; and the old-fashioned tuxedo found at the bottom of his trunk was altered by the same tailor. His fiancée did not dare to ask why Luzhin had formerly needed a tuxedo and an opera hat, fearing to arouse chess memories, and therefore she never learned about a certain big dinner given in Birmingham, where incidentally Valentinov... Oh well, good luck to him.

The renovation of Luzhin's envelope did not stop here. Shirts, ties and socks appeared — and Luzhin accepted all this with carefr